`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
`computeSunAngle` uses a cosine centered on noon (`cos(PI*(h-12)/12)`) — this is more accurate than a sine offset because it puts the peak naturally at h=12, horizon crossings at h=6 and h=18, and bottom at h=0/24. The formula scales by PI/2 so the zenith value matches the spec's stated maximum of PI/2 radians.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
