`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The midnight slot is intentionally the fallthrough case in `classifyTimeOfDay` — it's the only slot that wraps across the 0/24 boundary ([23,24) ∪ [0,5)). Putting it as an explicit `if` would require two range checks; as the `return "midnight"` default it covers both sides cleanly. The time slot boundaries are all config-sourced so they can be tuned (e.g., extending dawn to 6h) without touching logic.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

